==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Candleberry tree
<hw>Can"dle*ber`ry tree</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
shrub (the <spn>Myrica cerifera</spn>, or wax-bearing myrtle), common in
North America, the little nuts of which are covered with a greenish
white wax, which was formerly, used for hardening candles; -- also
called <altname>bayberry tree</altname>, <altname>bayberry</altname>, or
<altname>candleberry</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Candlebomb</ent>⟦br⟧
